seashore."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Clifton was born about 1305, in Stonyhurst, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William de Clifton, was 28 and his mother, Isabel de Huxley, was 25. He married Margaret Sherburne on 21 September 1348. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1365, at the age of 61."},"et":{"about 1305–1365":"umbes 1305–1365","1305–1365":"1305–1365","1320–1370":"1320–1370","1309–1365":"1309–1365","1330–1382":"1330–1382","1279–1329":"1279–1329","1282–1337":"1282–1337","1330":"1330","1382":"1382","1282":"1282","1370":"1370","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","after 1337":"pärast 1337","about 1305":"umbes 1305","1279":"1279","1365":"1365","21 September 1348":"21. september 1348","1320":"1320","1309":"1309","about 1298":"umbes 1298","1329":"1329","Clifton, Lancashire, England":"Clifton, Lancashire, England","Clifton, Cheshire, England":"Clifton, Cheshire, England","Stonyhurst, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Stonyhurst, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stonyhurst, Lancashire, England":"Stonyhurst, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"about 1305–1365":"noin 1305–1365","1305–1365":"1305–1365","1320–1370":"1320–1370","1309–1365":"1309–1365","1330–1382":"1330–1382","